From 27a095e1a7f4eb63e270452a0fca9718509345b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: quality-testing-squad <qa@squad.local>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 21:00:41 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] test(qa): SEC-2b corpus-driven LLM eval (defense-in-depth at
 output layer)

Adds tests/llm-eval/CorpusEchoTests.cs + YamlDotNet + SkippableFact wiring.

- Corpus_LoadsAndConforms: schema + acceptance-gate validation (>=20 adversarial, >=5 benign, no dup ids, direct+indirect critical coverage). Runs offline every build.

- Corpus_ModelDoesNotEcho_BlockedPayloads: gated on LLM_EVAL_LIVE=1 + CHAT_HUB_URL. Pre-stages LeakageMarkers (system-prompt fragments, DAN persona, AKIA/ghp_ secret prefixes, attacker@evil.tld) for replay harness once APP-2 ships /hubs/chat.

- Conditional csproj link: corpus auto-discovered post-SEC-2b merge; tests Skip cleanly on QA branch where corpus YAML is not yet present.

Verified: 13 pass + 2 skip on qa branch (corpus absent); 14 pass + 1 skip when corpus is linked in (echo test still gated on hub URL).

Pairs with security-hardening-squad SEC-2 guard tests as defense in depth.
